have had to
learn to step back and let them
be in charge.

28:20.799 --> 28:22.668 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
STUDENT: We got it.

28:22.701 --> 28:27.406 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN TULENKO: That's Gillette, a
good-size
city for Wyoming. But the rest
of the state

28:27.439 --> 28:32.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
looks more like this, tons of
open space and
very few people. That means the
schools out

28:32.978 --> 28:38.383 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
here are often very small, and
they face a
unique set of challenges in
implementing next

28:38.417 --> 28:40.519 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
generation science standards.

28:40.552 --> 28:46.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Wright Junior Senior High
School, 40 miles
south of Gillette, is a good
example. It has

28:46.558 --> 28:49.695 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
