to do it
all.

29:06.211 --> 29:08.046 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How many subjects do you teach
here?

29:08.080 --> 29:13.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH SEAMANDS: I teach four
subjects. I teach
anatomy, chemistry,
environmental science,

29:14.019 --> 29:14.853 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and physics.

29:14.886 --> 29:16.622 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN TULENKO: What's that like
for you?

29:16.655 --> 29:23.195 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SARAH SEAMANDS: It's
challenging. Some weeks,
I nail the chemistry and physics
and maybe

29:23.228 --> 29:30.235 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
environmental science, and then,
my anatomy
class, I neglect them.

29:30.268 --> 29:34.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So then I got to do really
interesting things
with anatomy, and then my
chemistry class

29:34.940 --> 29:37.109 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
